parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake rotor warping can lead to uneven braking, reduced stopping power, and increased risk of accidents. Warped rotors can also cause vibrations, noise, and uneven tire wear.
Rear brake noise can be a sign of worn or faulty brake components, which can lead to reduced braking performance and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rear brakes make noise when engaging
grinding or screeching sounds when braking

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or catch fire, leading to potential accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to be unable to shift gears, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle is unable to shift gears

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling at Idle after Continuous Long Drive
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling at idle can cause the vehicle to come to a sudden stop, increasing the risk of accidents, especially in heavy traffic or when exiting a highway.
symptoms: The engine idle speed drops to where the car stalls out after driving 50 miles on the highway
or encountering stop-and-go traffic; the car starts right back up when put into neutral and the key is turned.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The timing belt being off by one tooth can cause poor engine performance, including hard starts, which can lead to engine damage or failure.
